						               													<description>From the rules:&amp;#10;Junior SCRABBLE&amp;reg; Cards allow you to play two fun card games, based on the Junior SCRABBLE&amp;reg; game from Spear's Games. 'Words and Pictures' is a simple matching game for children aged 5 to 7, and 'Rainbow SCRABBLE&amp;reg;', for children Ages 7 - 10 is based on the classic SCRABBLE&amp;reg; game, with a simplified scoring system. Both games help children with their reading and word formation skills, and introduce them to the world of SCRABBLE&amp;reg;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Words and Pictures&amp;#10;The aim of the game is to collect the most Picture cards. Picture cards are won by placing the last letter of the word on the card.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Rainbow Scrabble&amp;#10;The aim of the game is to score the most points by forming words in a crossword fashion. Players make words by using the Letter cards, which have the same arrangement of letters as in Junior Scrabble.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Re-implements: &amp;#10;&amp;#10;    Scrabble Junior&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
